article.headline: Tennessee State 81, Fisk 76
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Rod Flowers scored 18 points and made a crucial late basket Thursday to lift Tennessee State over crosstown rival Fisk 81-76. Fisk had tied the game at 73-73, but Eric King made two free throws with 1:22 left and Flowers made a layup to put the Tigers up by four. Tennessee State (4-3) won its fourth straight game and broke a two-game losing skid to Fisk (1-2). Flowers also had a game-high 14 rebounds. Fisk led early in the game, but the Tigers took the lead for good 22-20 on a 3-pointer by Jeremy Jackson. It was 46-36 at halftime. Tennessee State's biggest lead was 49-38 with 19:10 left. Chris Adams led Fisk with 18 points. Aaron Hinton, Cedric Thomas, Jamor Washington and Jeremiah Williamson had 10 each. Bruce Price scored 15 for Tennessee State, Kareem Grant had 13 and Roshaun Bowens 10.
